Consolidated System Requirements

1. Security and Authentication
The system shall require secure authentication when users log into the system to protect sensitive financial information.
The system shall detect unauthorized access attempts, deny access, log the event, notify the user, and take appropriate security measures to protect the account.

2. Dashboard and Financial Overview
The system shall display a clear dashboard showing key financial information including income, expenses, remaining balance or budget, and important financial metrics to support quick financial review and decision making.
The system shall present financial summaries using simple, easy-to-read visual layouts to support users with varying financial experience.

3. Budget Monitoring and Alerts
The system shall allow users to compare their expenses to a predefined monthly budget.
The system shall generate alerts when spending approaches or exceeds predefined budget limits or category limits.
The system shall display a low-balance warning when an account balance falls below a user-defined threshold.

4. Transaction Management
The system shall automatically record transactions, subtract purchase amounts from the user’s balance, and update the remaining balance in real time.
The system shall validate transaction inputs and prevent submission of incomplete or invalid information.
The system shall warn users when a transaction exceeds the available account balance.

5. Expense Tracking and Categorization
The system shall automatically track and categorize transactions across accounts into predefined spending categories, including discretionary spending such as dining and entertainment.
The system shall highlight recurring expenses, subscriptions, unusual spending patterns, and fragmented purchases to help users better understand their spending behavior.

6. Reports and Data Review
The system shall generate clear financial reports and summaries with categorized expenses and spending trends.
The system shall allow users to filter and review transactions over customizable time periods.
The system shall allow exporting financial data or generating secure shareable reports.

7. Shared Financial Access and Collaboration
The system shall provide secure access controls that allow users to view shared financial accounts, share financial information with trusted family members, and support collaborative financial planning.
The system shall support shared expense tracking by allowing users to split costs and calculate individual contributions.

8. Savings Goals and Financial Planning
The system shall allow users to create savings goals, track progress through visual indicators such as percentages or progress bars, and calculate suggested monthly contributions.
The system shall support financial planning tools, including simulations that show how spending changes affect future savings.

9. Recurring Payments and Income Tracking
The system shall display recurring expenses, upcoming payments, and recent or upcoming income to provide users with a clear financial timeline.

10. Automation and Usability
The system shall automatically track expenses across multiple accounts with minimal manual input.
The system shall provide a clean, minimal interface that allows users to quickly view and manage their finances without complex setup or unnecessary steps.
